content: When I think of night view, it's the most popular and favorite place. It's not an exaggeration to say that it's the most beautiful night view in Korea. ... Really recommended!!
What did you do to say that it was a mountain, ㅎㅎ Eungbongsan Mountain with a back mountain feel! But when you go up, you can see the night view of Seoul at a glance. It's amazing 😌
The view of the Han River and Seoul Forest is wonderful. The mountain is low, so you can climb to the top in about 10 minutes. The view from the top is really amazing.
Located in the center of Seoul, it is a good place to walk. Overlooking Seoul and Han River. Especially spring is beautiful ~
You can go to subway line 3 and walk about 15 minutes after getting off. The night view is really beautiful.
In spring, the mountains are full of flowers. It's really beautiful. Very suitable for going with family~
This is simply a hidden treasure in the city center. Don't miss it if you want to enjoy the night view of Seoul~
Parking here is not very convenient, so it is recommended not to come by car.
The night view of Seoul is the best here! ! If you want to enjoy a peaceful night view, come here ^^
It takes about 30 minutes to reach the top of the mountain. The scenery during the day is average, but the night view is the best~~

This is a historical museum. It is a historical and artistic museum with local history as the content of the exhibition. It is still a scene of film shooting. Incheon Municipal Museum can choose the first attraction to go to, can understand the history of the whole person, not bad, there are some cultural relics inside, very beautiful, and it is worth seeing. It is quite big inside and needs to reserve two hours.

The Incheon City Museum, which opened in 1946, is a historic museum that displays historical importance from the Stone Age to modern times. It has special exhibitions throughout the year and also regularly hosts cultural performances. In the planning hall on the 2nd floor of the museum, there are sometimes exchange shows with other cities. If you visit Incheon, you can go here to learn about the history of Incheon and Korea!

Located in Songhedong, Naka-ku, Incheon City, it opened in 1946 and is the earliest public museum in South Korea. During the Korean War, the building was destroyed by gunfire. In 1953, the Songhedong Jiwupu Club was used as the new site. In 1990, the Incheon Municipal Museum moved to the foot of the cool mountain with a panoramic sea view. The museum's current architectural shape is designed as a branch stone tomb.
